In a bid to make the Ladoke Akintola University of Technology (LAUTECH), Ogbomoso, become a conventional university, the Oyo State governor, Engr. ‘Seyi Makinde, is considering a change of name for the popular University. If the state government’s plan sails through, the institution will be known as Ladoke Akintola University (LAU). This was disclosed by the State Attorney General and Commissioner for Justice, Prof. Oyelowo Oyewo, SAN, while speaking with journalists on Tuesday after the state executive council meeting at the Governor’s Office, Secretariat, Agodi in Ibadan. Acording to him, the state government will forward a Bill titled, ‘Ladoke Akintola University of Technology’ Amendment Bill to the Oyo State House of Assembly for consideration. Oyewo added the development was to accommodate other courses like Law, Humanities, among others. The briefing was attended by the State’s Commissioner for Information, Culture and Tourism, Dr. Wasiu Olatunbosun; Commissioner for Education, Science and Technology, Barrister Abdulraham Abdulraheem. When LEADERSHIP reached out to the spokesperson to Governor Makinde, Taiwo Adisa, he told our correspondent to await a formal press statement by the State government shortly.